2
00:02:15,372 --> 00:02:19,687
'He's known as Kat but his full name
is Stanislav Katczinsky.

3
00:02:24,847 --> 00:02:28,558
'but most of all for food
when there's none to be had.

4
00:02:34,802 --> 00:02:38,158
'My name is Paul Baumer.
I am 18 years old.

5
00:02:50,751 --> 00:02:53,628
'Josef Behm, who will study theology.

6
00:02:58,902 --> 00:03:01,780
'Albert Kropp, who will study law.

7
00:03:07,294 --> 00:03:10,536
'Friedrich Müller,
who will study everything.

8
00:03:16,645 --> 00:03:20,241
'Franz Kemmerich,
who will be a forester.

9
00:03:24,566 --> 00:03:28,278
'Peter Lehr,
who will travel and make love.

10
00:03:30,915 --> 00:03:34,991
'We are with our friends:
Tjaden, a locksmith before the war.

11
00:03:35,116 --> 00:03:37,034
'The biggest eater of the company.

12
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:46,145
'Westus, who dug peat for a living.
A good man to have on your side.

13
00:03:52,503 --> 00:03:54,776
'his farmyard and his wife.

14
00:03:59,456 --> 00:04:02,813
'They attack our trench.
We attack their trench.

15
00:04:02,813 --> 00:04:07,848
Then, to keep the score even, they
will attack our trench once again.

16
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:31,346
What are you doing? Wait.

17
00:07:31,471 --> 00:07:34,703
Over here. Here, over here.

18
00:07:34,703 --> 00:07:35,787
Quick.

19
00:07:45,377 --> 00:07:46,691
You'll be OK.

20
00:07:46,816 --> 00:07:50,412
OK, here we come. Come.

21
00:07:50,412 --> 00:07:51,851
Quick.

22
00:07:51,975 --> 00:07:54,488
Easy...easy.

23
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:05,766
It's his leg. He's lucky.

24
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:08,644
He'll be all right.

25
00:08:11,521 --> 00:08:13,199
He'll be all right.

26
00:08:16,671 --> 00:08:20,632
'You are our Iron Youth.'

27
00:08:20,632 --> 00:08:24,353
'Iron Youth becomes Iron Heroes.'

28
00:08:26,386 --> 00:08:30,826
It is my duty. Uh, it is my honour,

29
00:08:30,826 --> 00:08:36,820
to prepare you for the part
you must play in this great war.

30
00:08:36,945 --> 00:08:43,533
Our homeland has need
of men of character and strong will.

31
00:08:44,138 --> 00:08:47,370
It is my duty to prepare your minds

32
00:08:47,609 --> 00:08:51,810
so you will be better able
to train your bodies

33
00:08:51,925 --> 00:08:56,490
for your Kaiser, for your Fatherland,

34
00:08:57,564 --> 00:08:59,127
for your God.

35
00:09:12,199 --> 00:09:14,712
Germany is the nation of progress,

36
00:09:15,911 --> 00:09:17,474
the nation of culture...

37
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:22,144
the nation of science,
the nation of ideas...

38
00:09:25,021 --> 00:09:27,304
the nation of Beethoven,

39
00:09:28,388 --> 00:09:32,703
of Schiller, of Goethe...

40
00:09:34,382 --> 00:09:35,341
Baumer.

41
00:09:36,415 --> 00:09:37,374
Sir.

42
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:40,615
What is that?

43
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:42,534
A bird, sir.

44
00:09:42,658 --> 00:09:44,691
- A bird?
- Yes, sir.

45
00:09:44,691 --> 00:09:45,650
A lark?

46
00:09:45,775 --> 00:09:47,808
- Yes, sir.
- Very good.

47
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:49,007
On the window.

48
00:09:49,132 --> 00:09:51,050
- This line...
- The window.

49
00:09:51,165 --> 00:09:52,968
- Very exact.
- Thank you, sir.

50
00:09:54,406 --> 00:10:01,005
But you don't come here to draw,
to write poems...of to dream.

51
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,683
Do you Baumer?

52
00:10:02,683 --> 00:10:04,237
No.

53
00:10:06,999 --> 00:10:08,073
Sit down.

54
00:10:10,835 --> 00:10:14,911
Gentlemen, you have all passed
your examinations.

55
00:10:15,026 --> 00:10:17,433
As you know, you are graduated.

56
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:20,665
The time for class is over.

57
00:10:21,384 --> 00:10:25,105
The time for duty has begun.

58
00:10:27,618 --> 00:10:30,860
You are dismissed. Herr Baumer...

59
00:10:31,819 --> 00:10:33,142
You may stay.

60
00:10:48,851 --> 00:10:50,290
Cigarette?

61
00:10:51,728 --> 00:10:53,282
No, thank you, sir.

62
00:10:53,407 --> 00:10:54,720
Oh, you don't smoke.

63
00:10:54,845 --> 00:10:57,962
Well, it is not a good habit.

64
00:10:58,077 --> 00:11:01,319
But all good habits,
makes a dull person.

65
00:11:01,434 --> 00:11:03,112
What do the English say?

66
00:11:03,112 --> 00:11:06,114
- All work and no play makes...
- A dull man.

67
00:11:07,313 --> 00:11:09,595
A dull... Yes, yes, very good.

68
00:11:13,192 --> 00:11:15,944
There's a time for work and for play.

69
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:24,221
You are a dreamer, Baumer.

70
00:11:24,221 --> 00:11:27,702
You draw little sketches
and write little poems.

71
00:11:27,817 --> 00:11:32,018
But now you're a man,
you have your duties as a man,

72
00:11:32,018 --> 00:11:33,811
your duty to the Fatherland.

73
00:11:36,573 --> 00:11:40,409
Will you wait to be called up
of will you enlist?

74
00:11:40,534 --> 00:11:43,526
- Well...
- Of course, you'll respond to duty.

75
00:11:43,651 --> 00:11:45,569
You will all respond.

76
00:11:45,684 --> 00:11:50,364
The entire class will go
as one man to serve the Fatherland.

77
00:11:52,042 --> 00:11:55,524
I know I will be proud of you,
Baumer.

78
00:11:59,235 --> 00:12:01,038
'Today is wonderfully good.

79
00:12:01,153 --> 00:12:05,229
'Everyone has eaten for two men
and the mail has come.

80
00:12:05,469 --> 00:12:08,471
'The grasses sway like tall spears.

81
00:12:09,065 --> 00:12:12,671
'The white butterflies
float on the soft warm wind.

82
00:12:18,061 --> 00:12:20,104
'Let's not even think about it.

83
00:12:20,104 --> 00:12:22,377
'Let's just enjoy the world.

84
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:24,774
'Everything is new and brave.

85
00:12:24,899 --> 00:12:27,901
'Red poppies, the good food,

86
00:12:28,141 --> 00:12:31,373
'cigarettes and the summer breeze.'

87
00:13:09,744 --> 00:13:11,547
Paul? Paul?

88
00:13:15,623 --> 00:13:17,186
We're going to see Kemmerich.

89
00:13:42,725 --> 00:13:45,717
Nurse, can you tell me
where Franz Kemmerich is?

90
00:13:45,842 --> 00:13:47,760
Yes, he's through there.

91
00:13:59,269 --> 00:14:00,228
Franz.

92
00:14:02,031 --> 00:14:03,469
How are you?

93
00:14:04,303 --> 00:14:06,106
Someone stole my watch.

94
00:14:06,231 --> 00:14:08,504
- Bastards!
- I warned you, Franz.

95
00:14:08,629 --> 00:14:11,621
- I know.
- We'll tell the doctor.

96
00:14:13,664 --> 00:14:15,217
You'll be going home soon.

97
00:14:15,342 --> 00:14:16,656
Do you think?

98
00:14:20,013 --> 00:14:22,295
I feel... I'm all right.

99
00:14:25,652 --> 00:14:28,653
My foot. It's so painful.

100
00:14:29,852 --> 00:14:31,166
It's so cold.

101
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:35,002
That pain is your ticket home.

102
00:14:35,002 --> 00:14:37,764
You should be grateful
to that pain.

103
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,238
telling fat lies
to Katrine Hammerschmidt.

104
00:14:44,363 --> 00:14:48,554
Here's some smokes
and a piece of cheese from Kat,

105
00:14:48,678 --> 00:14:50,836
and your comb is in the tobacco tin.

106
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:54,193
Put them under the bed, please.

107
00:14:54,308 --> 00:14:58,633
Hide them.
You know they stole my watch.

108
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:06,545
Franz, will you be taking
these back home with you?

109
00:15:06,545 --> 00:15:08,463
Why not?

110
00:15:08,463 --> 00:15:11,695
Well, you don't really need
boots back home.

111
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:13,019
We could trade.

112
00:15:13,143 --> 00:15:16,500
- I've got...
- No! My mother gave me those.

113
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,492
- You could lend them to me?
- No.

114
00:15:19,492 --> 00:15:21,890
You'll be home a lot sooner than us.

115
00:15:27,289 --> 00:15:29,687
Orderly. Orderly!

116
00:15:29,812 --> 00:15:32,324
They don't come. They never come.

117
00:15:32,449 --> 00:15:33,523
We'll get someone.

118
00:15:33,523 --> 00:15:36,285
- It'll be different at home.
- When you return...

119
00:15:36,285 --> 00:15:38,922
- ..We'll be together.
- We'll come tomorrow.

120
00:15:39,162 --> 00:15:42,279
- I'll come tomorrow.
- Thank you. Thank you.

121
00:15:42,394 --> 00:15:45,521
I'll be back.

122
00:15:45,521 --> 00:15:47,678
Make sure you get my watch.

123
00:15:47,794 --> 00:15:48,877
We will.

124
00:16:09,142 --> 00:16:11,415
You think I don't care about Franz.

125
00:16:11,415 --> 00:16:12,738
Of course I care.

126
00:16:12,738 --> 00:16:18,732
If I could save his leg or life, I'd
walk over barbed wire. You know that.

127
00:16:18,857 --> 00:16:22,089
But where he's going,
he won't need his boots.

128
00:16:22,213 --> 00:16:23,767
He won't need anything.

129
00:16:23,892 --> 00:16:26,289
And my boots hurt. They really hurt.

130
00:16:26,404 --> 00:16:29,166
Why should some damn orderly
get his boots

131
00:16:29,282 --> 00:16:31,085
and not one of his friends.

132
00:16:33,003 --> 00:16:34,441
He's right, Paul.

133
00:16:42,238 --> 00:16:43,312
I know.

134
00:16:51,714 --> 00:16:53,392
Very good, Kemmerich.

135
00:17:01,179 --> 00:17:02,982
Very good, Kemmerich.

136
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:07,777
They've amputated my leg.

137
00:17:11,134 --> 00:17:12,697
Could be worse.

138
00:17:14,011 --> 00:17:17,128
Wegler lost his right arm,
which is very much worse.

139
00:17:19,046 --> 00:17:20,485
Besides, you're going home.

140
00:17:21,329 --> 00:17:22,767
Do you think so?

141
00:17:23,487 --> 00:17:25,050
Of course.

142
00:17:25,165 --> 00:17:26,968
Do you think so?

143
00:17:29,241 --> 00:17:30,919
Once you get over the operation.

144
00:17:33,796 --> 00:17:35,235
I don't think so.

145
00:17:38,716 --> 00:17:39,915
Don't talk nonsense.

146
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:47,232
I wanted to be a forester once.

147
00:17:51,069 --> 00:17:52,382
You will.

148
00:18:03,776 --> 00:18:05,819
You can do anything.

149
00:18:05,819 --> 00:18:10,854
If you find my watch, send it home.

150
00:18:13,855 --> 00:18:16,128
You'll go to a convalescent home.

151
00:18:17,087 --> 00:18:18,766
Maybe the one in Klosterberg.

152
00:18:21,883 --> 00:18:23,801
Remember how we hiked up there?

153
00:18:24,405 --> 00:18:25,604
Remember the poplars?

154
00:18:27,761 --> 00:18:29,919
The stream full of fish?

155
00:18:33,036 --> 00:18:39,030
Franz, Franz... When I come back,
we go up to the mountains again.

156
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:43,471
You can name all the trees for me.

157
00:18:43,471 --> 00:18:45,504
Tell me all about them.

158
00:18:47,911 --> 00:18:50,548
Franz, nothing will change.

159
00:18:52,102 --> 00:18:53,905
We'd be together again.

160
00:18:56,418 --> 00:18:57,377
Franz.

161
00:18:58,336 --> 00:18:59,295
Franz.

162
00:18:59,295 --> 00:19:06,497
Give...Müller...my...boots.

163
00:19:11,647 --> 00:19:15,723
Doctor? Doctor?
Where's the doctor? Doctor!

164
00:19:17,641 --> 00:19:18,840
Doctor!

165
00:19:18,964 --> 00:19:20,048
Where's the doctor?

166
00:19:20,883 --> 00:19:21,966
Doctor?

167
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,917
Doctor! Quickly,
Franz Kemmerich is dying.

168
00:19:26,042 --> 00:19:27,116
Which one's that?

169
00:19:27,116 --> 00:19:29,034
Bed 36, amputated leg.

170
00:19:29,034 --> 00:19:32,391
How should I know that?
I've amputated five legs today.

171
00:19:32,516 --> 00:19:33,954
You see to it.

172
00:19:37,196 --> 00:19:41,147
Today there have been sixteen deaths,
yours will be the seventeenth.

173
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:43,305
There'll probably be twenty
altogether.

174
00:19:47,026 --> 00:19:50,498
We must take him away at once.
We need the bed.

175
00:19:50,622 --> 00:19:52,905
They're lying on the floor outside.

176
00:20:12,325 --> 00:20:13,409
Paul.

177
00:20:13,409 --> 00:20:14,483
Yes, Mrs Kemmerich?

178
00:20:14,608 --> 00:20:17,725
- I want you to promise.
- What, Mrs Kemmerich?

179
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:20,122
- Look after Franz.
- Of course...

180
00:20:20,238 --> 00:20:24,074
He looks up to you.
He'll do anything you ask, you know?

181
00:20:24,198 --> 00:20:28,035
Make him stay away from danger.
You know how reckless he is.

182
00:20:28,159 --> 00:20:30,077
I'll make sure he behaves himself.

183
00:20:31,631 --> 00:20:33,070
God bless you both.

184
00:20:33,913 --> 00:20:35,352
Maria, Maria.

185
00:20:40,502 --> 00:20:42,190
Look after your brother.

186
00:20:42,190 --> 00:20:47,340
I'll see you soon. Take care.
Bye-bye, Mother, bye-bye.

187
00:20:47,465 --> 00:20:50,102
Right, come on, boys. Wake up!

188
00:20:50,217 --> 00:20:53,574
Let's go. Hey, wake up there.
Come on.

189
00:20:53,698 --> 00:20:56,211
Come on, come on, Come on!

190
00:20:56,336 --> 00:20:59,213
It's beautiful here. Come on.

191
00:20:59,338 --> 00:21:02,454
Let's go. Wake up. Food.

192
00:21:03,414 --> 00:21:04,612
Come on.

193
00:21:09,043 --> 00:21:13,004
Oh, Kat.
I don't know how you do it.

194
00:21:13,004 --> 00:21:15,162
Next time you come with me,

195
00:21:15,286 --> 00:21:17,559
I'll show you how to find food.

196
00:21:17,684 --> 00:21:20,197
When I'm not here,
it'll come in handy.

197
00:21:20,321 --> 00:21:22,000
What? You'll always be here.

198
00:21:22,115 --> 00:21:24,752
Ah, up here
'always' isn't a long time.

199
00:21:24,877 --> 00:21:27,629
Anyway, you'd better learn
so you won't go hungry.

200
00:21:27,754 --> 00:21:30,027
You pay attention to the teacher.

201
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:38,303
He's coming. He's coming.

202
00:21:40,106 --> 00:21:41,900
What did he want?

203
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,578
Doesn't matter. We're free.

204
00:21:43,703 --> 00:21:48,143
Time for work, for duty.
You will enlist, the entire class.

205
00:21:48,143 --> 00:21:50,656
Of course.
Behm, you too.

206
00:21:50,781 --> 00:21:54,013
- Maybe I can't. My eyes.
- They will.

207
00:21:54,013 --> 00:21:56,295
But not tonight.
Tonight we get drunk.

208
